<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-08-23T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-08-23T05:00:00-05:00" n="177" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d177">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">862.00/3061: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany (<persName type="from">Dodd</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-08-23T11:00:00+01:00">August
                                        23, 1933—11 a.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received August 23—7:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>133. Your 101, August 20, 7 p.m. I yesterday declined the invitation
                                on the ground that I could not absent myself from Berlin long enough
                                to have the pleasure of accepting and I understand that the French
                                and British will not go to Nuremberg.</p>
                            <p>Copy of my note sent by mail.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dodd</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>